James Anthony Dean (Ọnwa Februari ụbọchị asaa, afọ 1943 rụọ ọnwa Eprel ụbọchị itoolu, afọ 2006) bụ onye Amerịka na-ede egwu.  A maara ya nke ọma maka ọrụ ya na Motown Records n'ime afọ 1960s, mgbe mgbe ya na William Weatherspoon na-arụkọ ọrụ, onye ya na ya so dee ọtụtụ egwu gụnyere Jimmy Ruffin's "What Becomes of the Brokenhearted"
Dean dekwara, ya na John Glover, "You Don't Have to Be a Star (To Be in My Show)," a US no.1 hit for Marilyn McCoo and Billy Davis, Jr.

A mụrụ Dean na Detroit bụ nwa mbụ nke Richard na Dorothy Dean, ma gaa Hamtramck High School na Hamtramck, Michigan.  Ọ jere ozi na US Army, wee malite ịrụ ọrụ dị ka onye na-ede egwu maka Motown n'afọ 1964

Ya na William Weatherspoon jikọrọ aka dee egwu maka Jimmy Ruffin ("What Becomes of the Brokenhearted", "I've Passed This Way Before", "Farewell Is a Lonely Sound", "I'll Say Forever My Love", na "It's Wonderful (To Be Loved by You")); Marv Johnson ("I'll Pick a Rose for My Rose"); Edwin Starr ("I Am the Man for You Baby"); na ndị ọzọ.  Dean so dee "Everything Is Good About You Baby" nke The Supremes na Eddie Holland; Eddie na Brian Holland bụ ụmụ nwanne nna Dean.  Ya na Weatherspoon mepụtakwara "Mgbe ị bụ nwata na ịhụnanya", ihe egwu maka The Marvelettes

Ya na John Glover, Dean so dee maka The Four Tops, First Choice, na Marilyn McCoo na Billy Davis Jr., na-enwe ihe ịga nke ọma ya na ndekọ US nọmba nke mbụ nke afọ 1976 "You Don't Have to Be a Star (To Be in My Show)."
James Dean nwụrụ site na ọrịa kansa nke ọkpụkpụ azụ n'ụlọ ya na Detroit n'afọ 2006 mgbe ọ dị afọ iri isii na atọ.
